    "120772645": {
      "title": "Definition and Statistical Distributions of a Topological Number in the Lattice O(3) Sigma Model",
      "abstract": "Abstract We define a topological number Q for spin fields on a two-dimensional lattice. Q assumes integer values only and reduces to the well-known winding number in the classical continuum limit. A Monte Carlo measurement of the topological susceptibility \u03c7 t = \u3008 Q 2 \u3009 / volume on a 100 \u00d7 100 lattice reveals that it decreases exponentially with increasing \u03b2( = inverse bare coupling constant). The corresponding prediction of the perturbative renormalization group is not matched, however."
    }
